  "img": "systems/pf1/icons/feats/improved-counterspell.jpg",
  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelName\">The druid may cast a spell with a target of &ldquo;You&rdquo; on her animal companion (as a spell with a range of touch) instead of on herself. A druid may cast spells on her animal companion even if the spells normally do not affect creatures of the companion's type (animal). Spells cast in this way must come from a class that grants an animal companion. This ability does not allow the animal to share abilities that are not spells, even if they function like spells.&nbsp;</span></p>",
